Document: Range
Path: godot/classes/class_range.rst
Summary: Base class for nodes that represent a range of values.

Inherits: Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

The Range class is the base class for nodes that represent a range of values. This includes nodes like Slider, ProgressBar, and SpinBox. It provides common functionality for managing a value within a minimum and maximum boundary, including methods for setting and getting the value, and signals for when the value changes.

Properties:
allow_greater (bool): If true, the value can exceed the max value. Default: false.
allow_lesser (bool): If true, the value can be less than the min value. Default: false.
editable (bool): If true, the value can be edited by the user. Default: true.
exp_ratio (float): If greater than 0, the value changes exponentially. Default: 1.0.
focus_mode (int): Determines if the control can receive focus. Default: 2.
is_visible_in_tree (bool): Returns true if this node and all its ancestors are visible.
max_value (float): The maximum value of the range. Default: 1.0.
min_value (float): The minimum value of the range. Default: 0.0.
page (float): The size of a "page" for navigating the range. Default: 0.0.
step (float): The smallest unit the value can change by. Default: 0.0.
value (float): The current value of the range. Default: 0.0.

Signals:
value_changed(value: float)
value_is_zero()
value_changed_with_user_input(value: float, user_input: bool)
